package exec_06_01_compiler_assignment_pattern_positional_mismatch

## Semantics: positional struct mismatches yield an Error value (falsy).

struct Pair { i32, i32 }

fn main() -> void {
  value := Pair { 1, 2 }
  if Pair { first, second, third } := value {
    print("ok")
  } else {
    print("error")
  }
}
